<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="657">Novosti Sist. Vyssh. Rast.</emphasis>
21: 20. 1984) indicated 1254.2 (LINN) as type but this collection lacks the relevant 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="657">
<volumeTitle>Species Plantarum</volumeTitle>
</emphasis>
number (i.e. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“2”">&quot;2&quot;</normalizedToken>
) and was a post-1753 addition to the herbarium, and is not original material for the name. Johnson (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="657">Syst. Bot. Monogr.</emphasis>
11: 39. 1986) treated a Jussieu collection (No. 1599-A, P-JU) as the 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
but this material would not have been studied by Linnaeus and is not original material for the name either.
</paragraph>
